> Step aside, side salad: This hearty kale bowl is the stuff of lunch dreams.

Wash and dry produce.

Pat @Fully Cooked Chicken Breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; dice into
½-inch pieces. Place in a medium #microwave-safe bowl{} and toss with a
drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover
tightly with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until chicken is warmed through,
~{90%seconds}.

Meanwhile, remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into
bite-size pieces. Place kale and half the @shredded carrots{4%ounce} in a large
#bowl{}. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Using
your hands, massage kale and carrots (similar to how you would knead dough)
until kale leaves are tender, ~{1-3%minutes}.

In a small bowl, whisk together @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce},
@mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @sugar{}.

Add chicken and half the @dried cranberries{1%ounce} to bowl with kale and
carrots; toss with as much creamy dressing as you like.

Divide salad between shallow #bowls{}. Garnish with remaining cranberries and
serve.